by nicole ackerman page 1 slac association for student seminars cerenkov light imaging in biomedicine by nicole ackerman kavli 3rd floor conference room many physicists are familiar with how cerenkov light can be used in particle detectors and in astrophysics but biologists are now using the phenomena as well pet and spect imaging techniques only can image positrons and gamma rays so cerenkov luminescence imaging cli provides the first opportunity to directly image beta emitters which are of interest for therapeutic reasons additionally the optical imaging that is done for cli is more widely available and faster than pet so cli has some advantages in screening new pet probes in this talk i will cover the basics of cerenkov production why imaging of radioisotopes is needed in biomedicine and how cli has been used so far finally i will discuss the simulation work i have done on future uses of cli april 27 at 12 30
